cs.CE, cs.DC, cs.NA, cs.SE, cs.MS

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) as it deals with the analysis of portfolios of insurance/reinsurance risk using stochastic simulation techniques. It could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it explores parallel methods to speed up aggregate risk analysis. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as it proposes and implements an algorithm for analyzing aggregate risk. It may also fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) as it involves the implementation of the algorithm for multi-core CPUs and many-core GPUs. Finally, it could be classified under cs.MS (Mathematical Software) as it involves the development of software for performing simulations.
